<td align=right ><b>Overall</b></td>
<td nowrap ><img class=stars src=/imgs/star-lit.png><img class=stars src=/imgs/star-lit.png><img class=stars src=/imgs/star-lit.png><img class=stars src=/imgs/star-uli.png><img class=stars src=/imgs/star-uli.png> (2.75)</td>
</tr></table>
The <b>geodesic dome</b> is composed by straight structural elements, so called struts which themselves connect to hubs.
It's a rather complex approach, and one of it significance and advantage is it can be fine grained as required, at any size - that why "Size Flexibility" has the highest rating.
<br clear=both>
